{{refimprove|date=November 2015}} '''''Inside Series''''' is a set of short television movies produced by [[Bloomberg Television]] that features in-depth profiles of successful companies and their leaders.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bloomberg Television Features `Inside' Series|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/b/d2ed339b-8dc8-482a-b210-5851db76512e|publisher=Bloomberg Television|accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref> The series began streaming on [[Netflix]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=New on Netflix Streaming: Kevin Hart headlines a week of new releases|publisher=Examiner.com|date=January 10, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=You Made It to the Weekend! Here's What Is New on Netflix|url=http://okmagazine.com/meet-the-stars/you-made-it-to-the-weekend-heres-what-is-new-on-netflix/|publisher=OK Magazine|accessdate=12 November 2015|date=January 10, 2014}}</ref>
==TV Movies== * ''Inside: Chipotle'' (2013) - profiles [[Chipotle Mexican Grill]], an American restaurant chain * ''Inside: De Beers'' (2012) - profiles [[De Beers]] diamond company<ref>{{cite web|title=Inside De Beers|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/b/af61d822-b475-4a63-bb0b-87c441a6c61e|publisher=Bloomberg Television|accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref> * ''Inside: Dolce & Gabbana'' (2013) - profiles [[Dolce & Gabbana]], an Italian fashion company * ''Inside: LinkedIn'' (2013) - profiles [[LinkedIn]], a social networking service * ''Inside Lego'' (2014) - officially titled ''Brick by Brick: Inside Lego'', profiles [[The Lego Group]], a Denmark-based toy company<ref>{{cite web|title=Brick by Brick: Inside Lego|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/b/4a56e664-4427-49fc-82fb-2d5e4a6f4502|publisher=Bloomberg Television|accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref> * ''Inside: McDonald's'' (2013) - profiles [[McDonald's]], the world's largest chain of hamburger fast food restaurants * ''Inside: Pixar'' (2013) - profiles [[Pixar]], an American [[computer animation]] film studio owned by the [[Walt Disney Company]]
