'''Nickelodeon Sunday Movie Toons''' was a series of [[animated films|animated]] [[Television film|made-for-TV movies]], which lasted for just one season (2002) on [[Nickelodeon]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Grego|first1=Melissa|title=Tons of toons for Dic, Nick|url=https://variety.com/2002/tv/news/tons-of-toons-for-dic-nick-1117866653/|accessdate=2 June 2016|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=8 May 2002}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Godfrey|first1=Leigh|title=DIC And Nick Partner To Launch Sunday Movie Toons|url=http://www.awn.com/news/dic-and-nick-partner-launch-sunday-movie-toons|accessdate=2 June 2016|publisher=[[Animation World Network]]|date=9 May 2002}}</ref> It started on October 6, 2002 and ended on December 29, 2002. Produced by [[DIC Entertainment]], the made-for-TV films are either based on various DIC productions such as ''[[Inspector Gadget (1983 TV series)|Inspector Gadget]]'', ''[[Sabrina: The Animated Series]]'', and ''[[Dennis the Menace (1986 TV series)|Dennis the Menace]]'', or are loose adaptations of stories from classic literature such as ''[[Treasure Island]]'' and ''[[20,000 Leagues Under the Sea]]''. One film, ''[[Groove Squad]]'', which was about a group of crimefighting cheerleaders, was an original story. All of these films were later released to [[VHS]] and [[DVD]] in the U.S. by [[MGM Home Entertainment]] under the ''DIC Movie Toons'' label. In 2008, [[Gaiam]] re-released the films on DVD.
==List of movies== # ''[[Sabrina: Friends Forever]]'' (based on ''[[Sabrina: The Animated Series]]'') ({{Start date|10/6/02}}) # ''[[Inspector Gadget#Inspector Gadget.27s Last Case|Inspector Gadget's Last Case]]'' (10/13/02) # ''Time Kid'' (based on ''[[The Time Machine]]'' by [[H. G. Wells]]) (10/20/02) # ''Dennis the Menace: Cruise Control'' (based on the [[Dennis the Menace (1986 TV series)|1986–1988 animated series]] version of [[Dennis the Menace (U.S.)|Dennis the Menace]]) (10/27/02) # ''The Archies in Jugman'' (based on the [[Archie Comics|Archie]] universe as portrayed in ''[[Archie's Weird Mysteries]]'') (11/3/02) # ''[[Dinosaur Island (2002 film)|Dinosaur Island]]'' (based on ''[[The Lost World (Conan Doyle novel)|The Lost World]]'' by [[Sir Arthur Conan Doyle]]) (11/10/02) # ''My Fair Madeline'' (based on ''[[Madeline (TV series)|Madeline]]'') (11/17/02) # ''[[Groove Squad]]'' (11/24/02) # ''Treasure Island'' (based on ''[[Treasure Island]]'' by [[Robert Louis Stevenson]]) (12/1/02) # ''Charles Dickens' [[A Christmas Carol (1997 film)|A Christmas Carol]]'' (based on ''[[A Christmas Carol]]'' by [[Charles Dickens]]) (12/8/02) # ''Globehunters: An Around the World in 80 Days Adventure'' (based on ''[[Around the World in Eighty Days]]'' by [[Jules Verne]]) (12/15/02) # ''The Amazing Zorro'' (based on [[Johnston McCulley]]'s ''[[Zorro]]'') (12/22/02) # ''20,000 Leagues Under the Sea'' (based on ''[[20,000 Leagues Under the Sea]]'' by Jules Verne) (12/29/02)
