{{distinguish|Speed Zone}}

'''SpeedZone''', also known as '''Malibu''' and '''Malibu SpeedZone''' are the names of a group of [[motorsports]]-themed [[family entertainment center]]s throughout the United States. The chain includes two [[family]] [[racetrack]]s located in the City of [[Industry, California]] (within the [[Greater Los Angeles Area]]) and [[Dallas, Texas]]. Both of the facilities are owned by [[Palace Entertainment]] and were former [[Malibu Grand Prix]] tracks.

The following movies have been filmed at SpeedZone (City of Industry, California)

*''[[Guess Who (film)|Guess Who]]'' (Ashton Kutcher and Bernie Mac)
*''[[Clerks II]]'' (Jeff Anderson and Brian O'Halloran)

