{{Infobox film | name = The Ambitious Servant Girl | image = | border = | alt = | caption = | director = | producer = [[Christopher Muir]] | writer = | screenplay = | story = | based on = | starring =[[June Bronhill]] | music = | cinematography = | editing = | studio = [[Australian Broadcasting Commission]] | distributor = | released =1962 | runtime = | country = Australia | language = English | budget = | gross = }} '''''The Ambitious Servant Girl''''' is a 1962 TV play broadcast by the [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]. It was an opera and was directed by [[Christopher Muir]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article43202216 |title=GAY ITALIAN PERIOD OPERA |newspaper=[[The Australian Women's Weekly]] |volume=30 |issue=2 |date=31 October 1962 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |page=4 (Television) |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>
It starred [[June Bronhill]] and went for 40 minutes. It was shot in Melbourne.
